article.headline: W. Michigan 86, Michigan-Dearborn 45
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- All 13 players scored as Western Michigan cruised to an 86-45 victory over Michigan-Dearborn on Tuesday night. David Kool's 15 points led the Broncos (8-5), who won their fourth in a row. Reserves Flenard Whitfield added 14 and David Brown 13 as Western Michigan got 54 points from bench players. Donald Lawson pulled down 12 rebounds as Western Michigan piled up a 64-33 advantage over the NAIA Wolves (3-11). Le'Ante Duren led Michigan-Dearborn with 11 points. The closest the Wolves got was a 6-5 deficit after Matt Ponik's 3-pointer with 16:39 left in the first half. Western Michigan led 46-23 at intermission and did not let up in the second half. The gap reached 40 at 70-30 on Brown's layup with 11:33 left. The biggest lead was 46 points, at 86-40, on Muhammed Conteh's layup with 2:38 left.
